But the sprawling legislation includes consequential changes affecting one of America’s most distinctive characteristics: charitable giving. The United States has long been the world leader in charitable giving as a percentage of GDP, but, more […]
title: The ‘big, beautiful bill’ democratizes charitable giving

author: David Sivak
description: President Donald Trump is betting he can bring public opinion to his side in a winding legal fight with Harvard, the elite university that, more than any other, has resisted his sweeping policy demands. Harvard has sued the Trump administration twice for actions it says amount to a “campaign of retribution.” Its president, Alan Garber, […]
title: ‘Elite’ Harvard becomes Trump foil in widening legal fight

author: Kaelan Deese
description: Five former aides to President Joe Biden are facing the threat of subpoena ahead of a Thursday evening deadline to comply with a widening autopen investigation launched by House Republicans. House Oversight Committee Chairman James Comer (R-KY) is leading the investigation into whether Biden personally approved controversial last-minute executive actions, especially a series of preemptive […]
title: Deadline looms for ex-Biden aides to comply with GOP autopen investigation

author: Robert Goldberg
description: Gov. Gavin Newsom‘s (D-CA) Sacramento is spending like a drunken sailor, and it’s American taxpayers who are left with the hangover.  The governor’s latest budget “fixes” are less about fixing California’s real problems and more about siphoning off federal health dollars to paper over his own fiscal mismanagement. The result? Money meant for Medicare and […]
title: Gavin Newsom is robbing Medicare and hurting Californians

author: Washington Examiner Staff
description: Russia’s Minister of Foreign Affairs, Sergey Lavrov, suggested on Wednesday that a new round of peace talks be held to end the war in Ukraine.  Lavrov proposed holding talks in Istanbul, Turkey, on June 2. He emphasized his country’s previous demands specified in the earlier negotiations held in Istanbul on May 16, according to The […]
title: Russia suggests new peace talks with Ukraine to be scheduled in Istanbul

author: Washington Examiner Staff
description: Claims of bigotry, discrimination, and racist fan behavior after a WNBA game between the Indiana Fever and Chicago Sky earlier this month were not verifiable.  The game was played at Gainbridge Fieldhouse and featured a contentious matchup between league rivals Caitlin Clark of the Fever and Angel Reese of the Sky on May 17. After […]
title: WNBA unable to ‘substantiate’ claims of racism in its investigation

author: Washington Examiner
description: Harvard University and the federal government once shared a moral vision based on common values, and this was a mutually beneficial relationship. But those days are gone. Accordingly, the Trump administration’s decision to sever financial ties with Harvard is justified and necessary.  President Donald Trump’s administration signaled its intention on Tuesday to end remaining contracts with Harvard, worth an estimated $100 […]
title: Trump dumps Harvard

author: Ross O'Keefe
description: Rep. Nancy Mace (R-SC) used and directed staff to make burner accounts in order to bolster her online image, according to a Wired report. The South Carolina congresswoman chairs the House Subcommittee on Cybersecurity, Information Technology, and Government Innovation, knows how to code, and is one of the more computer-savvy members of the House. Former […]
title: Nancy Mace deployed burner accounts to counter online criticism, staffers claim

author: Kaelan Deese
description: A federal judge ruled Wednesday that the Trump administration’s effort to deport Mahmoud Khalil, a pro-Palestinian Columbia University student and legal U.S. resident, is likely unconstitutional. U.S. District Judge Michael Farbiarz said Secretary of State Marco Rubio’s justification for Khalil’s removal, that his beliefs and activism “compromise a compelling U.S. foreign policy interest,” fails constitutional muster, finding the underlying […]
title: Judge slams use of ‘vague’ law in pro-Palestinian Columbia student case

author: Ross O'Keefe
description: The Trump administration is reportedly asking some American companies to stop selling software used to design semiconductors to China. The United States is trying to make it more difficult for China to obtain semiconductors in order to rebuff its artificial intelligence advances. The Commerce Department told CNN on Wednesday it is “reviewing exports of strategic […]
title: Trump administration blocks several US companies from selling goods to China

author: Ross O'Keefe
description: FBI Director Kash Patel addressed questions about Jeffrey Epstein’s death and the files surrounding the convicted sex trafficker in a new interview. title: Patel ‘not going to rush’ to release Epstein files, doubles down on sex trafficker’s suicide

author: Ross O'Keefe
description: Secretary of State Marco Rubio says the Trump administration will begin “aggressively” revoking visas of Chinese students, including those studying in “critical fields.” The announcement also prioritizes revoking the visas of those with connections to the Chinese Communist Party and came in a statement titled “New Visa Policies Put America First, Not China.” “Under President […]
title: Visas of Chinese students to be ‘aggressively’ revoked, Rubio says
